{"config":{"lang":["fr"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"Learn Linux","text":"<p>Formation Linux en 6 modules : de la d\u00e9couverte \u00e0 la mise en pratique.</p>"},{"location":"#programme-de-formation-6-modules","title":"Programme de formation (6 modules)","text":"Module Th\u00e8me Contenu principal 1 D\u00e9couverte et bases Qu\u2019est-ce que Linux, pourquoi l\u2019utiliser, bases du syst\u00e8me, installation. Structure des fichiers, commandes de base, liens, montage, espace disque. 2 Syst\u00e8me : permissions, processus, disques Propri\u00e9taires, groupes, chmod, chown, umask, ACL, utilisateurs, sudo. Processus, signaux, priorit\u00e9s, jobs, cron, systemd, logs. Types de FS, partitionnement, LVM, swap, fstab, inodes. 3 Logiciels et shell Gestionnaires de paquets (apt, yum, pacman), d\u00e9p\u00f4ts, compilation. Bash/zsh, variables, conditions, boucles, fonctions, redirections, pipes, automatisation. 4 R\u00e9seau IP, DNS, sous-r\u00e9seaux. Commandes (ping, ss, ip). SSH, pare-feu (iptables, nftables), scp, rsync. 5 S\u00e9curit\u00e9 et administration Privil\u00e8ges root, authentification, s\u00e9curisation des services, SELinux/AppArmor, chiffrement. Journaux, monitoring, sauvegarde, virtualisation, conteneurs, ulimits, cgroups. 6 Projets et approfondissement Projets : backup, serveur web, gestion users, monitoring, archivage logs. Suite : noyau, contribution open source, DevOps/cloud, performances et s\u00e9curit\u00e9 avanc\u00e9e."},{"location":"#ressources","title":"Ressources","text":"<ul> <li>Roadmap Linux</li> </ul>"},{"location":"01-introduction/01-qu-est-ce-que-linux/","title":"Qu'est-ce que Linux ?","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger (histoire, distributions).</p>"},{"location":"01-introduction/02-pourquoi-linux/","title":"Pourquoi utiliser Linux ?","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger (serveurs, dev, administration).</p>"},{"location":"01-introduction/03-bases-systeme/","title":"Les bases du syst\u00e8me Linux","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger (noyau, shell, architecture).</p>"},{"location":"01-introduction/04-installation/","title":"Installation (VM, dual boot, WSL)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"02-fichiers/01-structure-fichiers/","title":"Structure du syst\u00e8me de fichiers Linux","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger (/, /etc, /home, hi\u00e9rarchie FHS).</p>"},{"location":"02-fichiers/02-commandes-base/","title":"Commandes de base (ls, cd, pwd, cp, mv, rm, mkdir)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"02-fichiers/03-liens-symboliques/","title":"Liens symboliques et hard links","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"02-fichiers/04-montage-disques/","title":"Montage et d\u00e9montage (mount, umount)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"02-fichiers/05-espace-disque/","title":"Analyser l'espace disque (du, df)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"03-permissions/01-proprietaires-groupes/","title":"Propri\u00e9taires, groupes, UID / GID","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"03-permissions/02-permissions-chmod-chown/","title":"Permissions : chmod, chown (octal vs symbolique)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"03-permissions/03-umask-acl/","title":"umask et ACL (Access Control Lists)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"03-permissions/04-utilisateurs-groupes/","title":"Utilisateurs et groupes (useradd, usermod, groupadd\u2026)","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"03-permissions/05-sudo/","title":"sudo et escalade de privil\u00e8ges","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"04-processus/01-processus-ps-top/","title":"Processus : ps, top, htop","text":"<p>Contenu \u00e0 r\u00e9diger.</p>"},{"location":"04-processus/02-signaux-kill/",